<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine - Model Years Late 1997 to 2003 - Cylinder Head And Valves -
        Cleaning
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Cleaning</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Crankcase</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean the crankcase to cylinder head mating surface of any gasket material, dirt, grease
                    and any other foreign deposits.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para></para>
                    <para>To avoid damage to the engine, clean dirt in threads or replace any damaged bolts with
                        equivalent sized, phosphate coated bolts with a 10.9 hardness grade. Damaged threads may cause
                        binding and result in a false torque reading.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a bottoming hand tap (M12 x 1.75) to clear the cylinder head mounting bolt threads
                    of all grease, dirt, and other deposits.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Wash all cylinder head bolts with a suitable solvent and dry them thoroughly.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
